text: Progreso is a corregimiento in Barú District, Chiriquí Province, Panama. It has a land area of and had a population of 11,402 as of 2010, giving it a population density of . Its population as of 1990 was 13,107; its population as of 2000 was 10,103. Its inhabitants are mainly engaged in planting and harvesting Rice. ==References== Category:Corregimientos of Chiriquí Province
title: Progreso, Chiriquí
